cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and proposes metrics to describe a collection of texts.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the proposed metrics could be useful in information retrieval tasks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the correlation between the proposed metrics and text classification performance of a machine learning model.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with quantitative measures for text collections, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes metrics to measure dispersion, sparsity, and uniformity of a text collection, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
